Corner Old Coast Road & Oakleigh Drive

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
MIXED USE / RESIDENTIAL / MEDICAL / RETIREMENT R80

Located next to Erskine Central Shopping Centre Mandurah, this 12,121sqm* combined parcel of  land is for sale 'in one line' or as individual lots of 9,914sqm*, 1,107sqm* and 1,110sqm*.

Zoned Mixed Use/ Residential R40 with Medical Centre and Retirement Village also permitted within the approved ODP, the subject site has a broad range of additional uses considered, including Child Care, Civic Use, Corner Shop, Display Home Centre, Kindergarten, Nursing Home, Place of Public Worship, Public Utility, Serviced Apartment (STCA)

Offers Invited closing Thursday 12th May 2016.

CONSTRUCT   COMPLETE   CAPITALISE

CB Richard Ellis is delighted to have the opportunity of offering for sale 3 Veneto Lane, one of Mandurah Ocean Marina's landmark development sites.

The property comprises a partially completed multi level apartment development with spectacular views to the southeast over La Volta Canal to the Mandurah Inlet and to the west out over the Indian Ocean. (Upper level views only)

Present development is to a third floor plate height where construction has ceased. Approval was for a 6 level residential development comprising 11 luxury apartments, 9 of which where commenced, ranging from 2 bedroom x 2 bathroom to 4 bedroom x 2 bathroom apartments.  The development also comprises 19 car bays on the ground floor.

The opportunity exists for a builder, developer or syndicate of owners to purchase "As Is" and complete the development in accordance with the current plans, or if seen fit, amend the development and ultimately prosper from the sale of individual apartments as the residential property market improves.

SALE PROCESS
The property is being offered for sale on behalf of PPB, Receivers and Managers appointed, by the Offers Invited Process with submissions closing at 2pm Friday 20th November 2009.

DETAILS
To discuss further and to obtain a detailed Information Memorandum or contract,
please contact exclusive selling agents:

Murray Davies - 0409 885 099

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Landmark Development Site - Mandurah Ocean Marina

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present for sale the Kannis Centre at 25-27 Mandurah Terrace, Mandurah situated on the high-Exposure corner of Mandurah Terrace and Smart Street in the heart of the Mandurah waterfront and tourism precinct.

The site presents an excellent value-add opportunity for the astute investor, with the potential to upgrade and enhance the existing buildings to maximise the income potential with further opportunity to fully redevelop in time up to 5 storeys, ideal for a prominent mixed-use development with exceptional main street frontage suited to lower level retail upper level residential uses.

1,217sqm* two storey building currently comprising 12 individual tenancies

1,250sqm* corner land parcel with extensive Smart Street and Mandurah Terrace frontages

Zoned ‘City Centre Development’ the property is ideally positioned for future upgrade or complete redevelopment

Overlooking the Mandurah foreshore, the building is well-complimented by nearby retail and entertainment offerings including Woolworths, Gloria Jeans, Redmanna Waterfront and The Brighton Hotel, plus many more specialty retailers.

The City of Mandurah has recently spent $17 million on a makeover of the Mandurah foreshore, creating a vibrant streetscape by the waterfront. 

The local government is also in the process of advancing plans to upgrade the adjacent Smart Street mall, set to improve the appearance and presentation of Smart Street with a focus to activate and provide for pedestrian-based activity.

This property is now under offer. For further information, please contact exclusive selling agents CBRE.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: PRIME MAINSTREET CORNER LOCATION - VALUE-ADD RETAIL INVESTMENT

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE and Raine & Horne Mandurah are pleased to present this prominent high exposure and versatile corner development site adjoining BP Service Station and directly opposite the newly upgraded Mandurah Forum Shopping Centre.

The site boasts tremendous south western corner frontage of over 45metres* to Pinjarra Road and over 70meters* to Dower Street with an eastern frontage of over 40metres* to Parkview Street.

The property sits on a single title however subject to two distinct zonings. Pinjarra Road/Dower Street portion approximately 3,821sqm* zoned Service Commercial and the Parkview Street portion of approximately 2,224sqm* currently zoned Residential. Suitable uses include Fast Food, Showroom, Medical, Childcare & Residential.

We note that under the proposed Town Planning Scheme No 12, the City of Mandurah is considering a change for both portions that will result in a Commercial & Residential Mixed-Use zoning. This will add significant development options, particularly for the current Residential portion fronting Parkview Street.

This exceptional development site opportunity is for sale via an Offers Invited campaign closing Thursday June 4th 2020 at 2pm WST.

For further information, please contact the exclusive sales and marketing agent's Raine & Horne Mandurah - Peter Vetten 0403584466 or CBRE - Jake Wallman 0403975298 and Ben Younger 0410533679

*approx

CBRE is pleased to present for sale this prominently located vacant development site, comprising three individual titles at 64 & 65 Mandurah Terrace and 42 Sholl Street, Mandurah.

Providing 3 prominent street frontages including over 40m* to Mandurah Terrace overlooking the Mandurah foreshore, 104m* to Cooper Street and over 20m* to Sholl Street, the combined land parcel boasts a significant land footprint of 3,205sqm*.

Zoned ‘City Centre Development’, the two Mandurah Terrace sites have a maximum height limit of 5 storeys, whilst the rear Sholl street site has a maximum height of 8 storeys.

Potential uses include: RETAIL I DINING AND ENTERTAINMENT I RESIDENTIAL I SENIORS LIVING I MIXED USE I COMMERCIAL I CULTURAL.

This prominent waterfront opportunity is located 150metres* from Dome Café’, and within walking distance to nearby Cicerello’s, San Churros, Mandurah Boardwalk, Han’s cafe and a host of other retail, cultural and entertainment offerings surrounding Administration bay. 

We present buyers with a rare opportunity to acquire a prominent foreshore development site with excellent connectivity to the Mandurah foreshore precinct and the adjacent Mandurah Marina.

The lots are available for sale via ‘Offers to Purchase Invited’ closing Thursday 11th April 2019 at 4:00pm.

To discuss in detail and to obtain further information please contact the exclusive selling agents.
